H0.text: General Charles de Gaulle was French President 1959 to 1969. Who succeeded him. Alain Poher

H1.text: General Charles de Gaulle was French President 1959 to 1969. Who succeeded him. François Mitterrand

H2.text: General Charles de Gaulle was French President 1959 to 1969. Who succeeded him. Valéry Giscard d'Estaing

H3.text: General Charles de Gaulle was French President 1959 to 1969. Who succeeded him. George Pompidou

A4.text: After the failure of the 1969 constitutional referendum, de Gaulle resigned and Pompidou was elected president of France.

A5.text: In the general election of 15 June 1969, he defeated the centrist president of the Senate and acting president Alain Poher by a wide margin (58% to 42%).
